.TH "reserve_top_address" 9 "reserve_top_address" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
reserve_top_address \- reserves a hole in the top of kernel address space @reserve - size of hole to reserve
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" reserve_top_address
.BI "(unsigned long reserve "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "reserve" 12
-- undescribed --
.SH "DESCRIPTION"

Can be used to relocate the fixmap area and poke a hole in the top
of kernel address space to make room for a hypervisor.
